  "message": "Message sent to luca-palmieri's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "steve-krug",
    "senderColor": "cyan",
    "target": "@luca-palmieri",
    "targetColor": "blue",
    "summary": "Approved Luca as Step 9 driver, UX notes on clarify flow",
    "content": "CONSENSUS: APPROVED for Luca continuing as Driver for Step 9.\n\nStep 9 (Clarify as Waiting For) builds directly on the Step 8 Waiting For infrastructure you just built. Continuity makes sense -- you have full context on the domain types, routes, and templates.\n\nFrom a UX perspective, the key thing for Step 9 is the clarify form on `/inbox/{id}/clarify`. We already have clarify paths for Next Action and Project. Adding \"Waiting For\" as a radio button destination should follow the same progressive disclosure pattern: user selects \"Waiting For,\" and the relevant fields appear (waiting_on person). The transition from inbox item title to waiting-for item title should feel seamless -- the title carries over, the user just adds who they're waiting on.\n\nLooking forward to reviewing the design proposal."
  }
}
